Definition: cloud computing is the on-demand delivery of the compute power, database storage, application, and other IT resources
Pay-as-you-go pricing

Deployment Models of cloud
1. private cloud
2. public cloud 
3. hybrid cloud

Five Characterstics of cloud computing
1. on-demand self services
2. Broad network access
3. Multi-tenancy and resources pooling
4. Rapid elasticity and scalability
5. Measured service

SIX advantages of cloud computing
1. Teade CAPEX for operational expenses
2. Benefit from massive economies scale
3. stop guessing capacity
4. Increase speed and agility
5. Stop spending money running and maintaining data ceters
6. Go global in minutes


Types
1. IaaS
2. PaaS
3. SaaS

Pricing of Cloud 
1. Compute
2. Storage
3. Data transfer OUT of the cloud

